HEADWORD: Noctambulation
<hw>Noc*tam`bu*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nox</ets>, <ets>noctis</ets>, night + <ets>ambulare</ets> to walk:
cf. F. <ets>noctambulation</ets>.]</ety> <def>Somnambulism;
sleepwalking; walking in one's sleep.</def> <rj><au>Quain.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
